Definition of terms for the pro-extantial ethic

    pro-extantial
        ─ adjective
            - promoting continued existence
        : cf. https://doi.org/10.1093/OED/7770661153 : Oxford English Dictionary, s.v. “extant (adj.),
          sense 4.b,” September 2024.  ‘Continuing to exist; that has escaped the ravages of time,
          still existing.’



